cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.MM 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely sub-category as the paper deals with image stylization and uses deep features for content and style representation. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper uses adversarial networks for regularization and learning intrinsic properties of image styles. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible sub-category as the paper proposes a fast feed-forward network for arbitrary style transfer. 
4. cs.GR (Graphics) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with generating stylized images. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible sub-category as the paper deals with image stylization and proposes a mask module for spatially deciding the stylization level.
